urlText: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.
content:

If travelling onto Goulburn, or other Opal enabled station along the Southern Highlands Line, you should not tap off when transferring from Coach to an Intercity train but instead tap off at your destination station.

Booking is not required for Opal customers on this route.

urlText: Moore Park busway, bus stop closures
content:
Each night between 10pm and 5am on Monday 19, Tuesday 20 and Wednesday 21 April 2021, Sydney Light Rail rectification works will see the temporary closure of the Moore Park busway, with the following stops affected:
  • Bus stop Moore Park busway at Robertson Rd (202138) will be closed. The alternative stop is Anzac Pde opposite Robertson Rd (202111) for routes 339, 373, 374 and 377 towards City Circular Quay.
  • Bus stop Moore Park busway at Lang Rd (202144) will be closed. The alternative stop is Anzac Pde opposite Robertson Rd (202111) for routes 339, 373, 374 and 377 towards City Circular Quay.
  • Bus stop Moore Park busway after Alison Rd (203348) will be closed. The alternative stop is Alison Rd before Doncaster Ave (203143) for routes 339, 373, 374 and 377 towards City Circular Quay.
subtitle: Moore Park busway, bus stop closures
